Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a data-driven approach to household archaeology, which involves using machine learning algorithms to analyze the data. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
2. cs.CL - The paper involves natural language processing techniques to extract information from textual descriptions of the objects found in Pompeian households. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics.
3. cs.DB - The paper involves the use of a database of objects discovered in Pompeian households to study the structure of Roman households. This falls under the domain of databases.
4. cs.IR - The paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques to extract information from textual descriptions of the objects found in Pompeian households. This falls under the domain of information retrieval.
5. cs.LG - The paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the data and make predictions about the structure of Pompeian households. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
